{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos377.erdos_377 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos377.erdos_377.","id":"vf_7dfa290f4c2e8aae","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #377: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Is there some absolute constant $C>0$ such that\\[\\sum_{p\\leq n}1_{p\\nmid \\binom{2n}{n}}\\frac{1}{p}\\leq C\\]for all $n$ (where the summation is restricted to primes $p\\leq n$)? Current best: A question of Erd\\H{o}s, Graham, Ruzsa, and Straus \\cite{EGRS75}, who proved that if $f(n)$ is the sum in question then\\[\\lim_{x\\to \\infty}\\frac{1}{x}\\sum_{n\\leq x}f(n) = \\sum_{k=2}^\\infty \\frac{\\log k}{2^k}=\\gamma_0\\]and\\[\\lim_{x\\to \\infty}\\frac{1}{x}\\sum_{n\\leq x}f(n)^2 = \\gamma_0^2,\\]so that for almost all integers $f(m)=\\gamma_0+o(1)$. (It is trivial from Mertens estimates that $f(n)\\leq (1+o(1))\\log\\log n$.)  A positive answer would imply that\\[\\sum_{p\\leq n}1_{p\\mid \\binom{2n}{n}}\\frac{1}{p}=(1-o(1))\\log\\log n,\\]and Erd\\H{o}s, Graham, Ruzsa, and Straus say there is 'no doubt' this latter claim is true. Prize: no. Tags: binomial coefficients, number theory.","id":"vf_edaeb47ea470d9ba","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős 377 (is ∑_{p<=n, p∤C(2n,n)} 1/p bounded?) is confirmed OPEN — not settled here. Verified contributions: (i) exact Kummer reformulation f(n)=∑ 1/p over primes p that are \"p-flat\" (all base-p digi","claimed_status":"verified_computationally","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_c1765b482889d28d","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_c1765b482889d28d","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":